The original interest in the property came from old school prospecting realising that many of the boulders and transported rocks were vein material carrying gold.

Visible gold found by the author within a populous boulder field. Vein quartz boulders when weathered can be difficult to distinguish from siliceous quartzite/conglomerate. Hence the reason the density of the vein boulders went unappreciated for so long.
Heavy machinery trench around vein boulders locally mapping bedrock and till profiling.
